# Copy this file to ".env" in the same folder (backend/.env) and fill in your keys.
# Without ANY of these, PRISM runs entirely on rule-based/simulated fallback logic
# (still works end-to-end for a demo, just not "live" — every generated field
# will show ai_generated: false, and delivery fields will show *_real: false).

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1) CONTENT GENERATION — pick ONE provider (powers L0/L1/L2/L3/L4 reasoning + text)
#
# Option A: Gemini (free tier, but only ~5 requests/minute on flash — easy to
# hit while clicking around during a demo)
# Get a FREE key at: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-key-here
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# Option B: NEAR AI Cloud (pay-per-token, no aggressive per-minute limit —
# better for live demos with lots of clicking. Cheap: a few dollars of
# credit covers thousands of PRISM's calls)
# Get a key at: https://cloud.near.ai/
# NEAR_AI_API_KEY=
# NEAR_AI_MODEL=deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-V3.1

# Which provider to use: "gemini", "nearai", or "auto" (prefers NEAR AI if
# its key is set, since it has no per-minute rate limit)
# PRISM_AI_PROVIDER=auto

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2) VOICE DELIVERY — Sarvam AI (free trial, genuinely synthesizes real audio)
# Get a key at: https://dashboard.sarvam.ai/  (API Keys section)
# SARVAM_API_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3) WHATSAPP DELIVERY — Meta WhatsApp Cloud API (free test tier)
# Setup (~10 min, no business verification needed for testing):
#   1. https://developers.facebook.com/apps -> Create App -> add "WhatsApp" product
#   2. WhatsApp > API Setup screen gives you a free TEST number, a temporary
#      access token, and a Phone Number ID
#   3. In the same screen, add YOUR OWN phone number to the "To" test list
#      (Meta only allows messaging numbers you've explicitly added in test mode)
# IMPORTANT: WhatsApp only allows freeform text within 24h of the recipient
# messaging you first, OR via a pre-approved template. PRISM automatically
# falls back to Meta's pre-approved "hello_world" template so real delivery
# still works even outside that window — see whatsapp_client.py for details.
# WHATSAPP_TOKEN=
# WHATSAPP_PHONE_NUMBER_ID=
# WHATSAPP_TEST_RECIPIENT=          # e.g. 91XXXXXXXXXX — must be in your test "To" list

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4) REAL GOVERNMENT DATA — data.gov.in Open Government Data Platform (free)
# Covers: Agmarknet (real mandi/crop prices) + PMJDY (real financial-inclusion
# account data) — both genuinely real, at DISTRICT level (not per-pincode,
# since no public dataset breaks down that granularly).
# NOT included: DBT Bharat and GST registration data have no public API at
# usable granularity — PMJDY is used as the honest real proxy instead.
#
# Setup (~5 min):
#   1. Register free at https://data.gov.in/user/register
#   2. Get your API key at https://data.gov.in/user (My Account -> API Key)
#   3. Search "Agmarknet" and "PMJDY district" on data.gov.in, open a matching
#      resource, and copy its resource_id (shown on the resource's API tab)
# DATA_GOV_IN_API_KEY=
# AGMARKNET_RESOURCE_ID=
# PMJDY_RESOURCE_ID=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOT REAL-ABLE, BY DESIGN — these stay clearly-labeled simulations because
# no individual or hackathon team can obtain what they'd actually require:
#   - USSD delivery: needs a paid telecom aggregator agreement (Airtel/BSNL)
#   - BC agent dispatch: needs an actual employed human workforce
#   - DBT Bharat / GST registration data: no public API exists
